<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">THE EASIEST WAYS FOR NON-ROGUES TO UNDERSTAND EVADE:<br>
Evade is the opposite of taunt.  <p>

Its that simple.  But it cant be used while the rogue is actually attacking.  And it happens to use the same button as hide.  <p>

When a rogue hits hide during a battle and he is not attacking it actually processes as evade.  If it is successful then the rogues hate rating is lowered (healers understand hate ratings those are the things that make a monster rip through the entire party to smack a caster).  Anyway with taunt a warrior makes his hate rating go up.  With evade a rogue makes his hate rating go down.  If it goes down below somebody else beating on the monster the monster will turn and attack that other thing.  <p>

It is a skill that can be abused by a cowardly rogue.  There are lots of stories about rogues being the only surviver.... gee i wonder why.  Was it becuase he used evade constantly.   probably.  I like to use it after i have taken my quota of damage and when i need to backstab.  I figure with evade i can afford to take a certain amount.   The absolute worst time to evade is when it is just you in the caster.  If you evade then the caster will have a hell of a time getting to attack you again.<p>

opposite of taunt though was the short answer</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
