<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Using evade constantly is cowardly?  You obviously don't know much about your rogue if you think this.  That's just plain dumb.  Rogues job in a group = do as much damage as you can as fast as you can.  And that means that you should be staying behind the mob the ENTIRE fight if you can.  If you have a warrior/pally/sk etc in your group, they are there to take the damage, not the rogue.  You cause less there to be less total damage inflicted to your group my killing of the mobs as fast as possible by backstabbing.  And guess what, if you're taking the hits, you're stressing out the healer, and NOT backstabbing.  If you want to play outside your role and get smacked around a bit, go for it, but if I were the tank in the group, and I saw you weren't evading, I wouldn't be particularly happy with your playing style.  Anyone in your group who knows as much about rogues as I do would feel the same way--simple as that.<p>

Anonymous Lvl 56 Blackguard</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
