<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I usually play with a bard and its just plain ineffiecient to not take damage as a rogue.  Yes the warrior is there to take damage but with a bard the damage is recovered faster if it is spread out over the whole group.  Secondly and i swear by this: AS LONG AS THE TANK IS HEALTHY THE GROUP IS HEALTHY.  I can get by on 3 bubbs at the start of the fight specifically becuase of evade but if a fight starts and the warrior is STILL at 3 bubs thats a bad sign.  ITs a sign that mobs are stressing the group. If the next fight starts and you are 100% and the warrior is still at 3 bubs you have to play with the mix a little.  Basically all i am saying is that a rogue has to manage his health becuase he is one of the few classes that can.  Actually he is the only class that can make the baddies turn away from him.  Further about healers... i usually tell the healers not to heal me unless they just are pouring mana out their weat glands.  I DONT NEED IT becuase of evade.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
