<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Clerics complete heal the tanks.  Rogues do the damage and avoid the need for heals.  Tanks take damage and keep mobs off the other group members.  Bards play mana song.  Everyone else fills their roll.  It's as simple as that.  A cleric can complete heal 5, maybe 6 times with full mana.  Taking a few hits as a rogue (which is all you can really take before needing a heal) is not worth the cleric's extra mana, which should be dedicated to keeping the tank on his feet.  This hopefully keeps the mob off any other group members if your tank is halfway competent, and makes the healer's job easy because he only has to watch one person's health.  Bards are not there to heal your group, it's just regen, and I don't remember the last time I've had a bard play that song anyway.  Once again, I know what I'm talking about, and I get complemented on not ever getting hit by people who know anything about rogues, because they know I'm doing my job:  doing the most damage I possibly can.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
