<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Vantose, while there is a small portion in that, you still are giving some horrible tips here.  First of all, look at your level (36) and mine (56).  I fight much harder stuff than you do.  I wait till I'm almost dead to evade, and one failure means I'm dead.  Even if I just wait till I'm getting attacked, a couple of fails mean I'm dead.  Evade has a 10 second refresh time.  I can't handle most mobs I fight for 20 seconds without a heal, and that's a waste of a cleric's mana.  And as for monks being better able to turn a mob away, are you talking about feign death?  That's stupid, no good monk is going to feign death when the whole group is still going, and guess what, if the monk gets back up, whoops! he's top of the aggro list again!  Rogues aren't the ONLY class who can turn a mob away either, though they are the most efficient at it.  There are spells that cause the same effect as evade--wizards, rangers, etc.  Think about what you say before you say dumb stuff like that.  Yes bards can do more than play mana song, I was just saying that they usually play that rather than regen.  I don't remember the last time I heard regen song.  If you wanted to be a tank for "years and years", you chose the wrong class buddy.  You will be a horrible rogue post 50, you will die too much and you will annoy your group members because of all the down time.  Rogues CANNOT tank at my level, and at your level it's also not a very intelligent thing to do.  You don't go into groups to get smacked around.  When people want a tank for their group, they don't look for a rogue.  They look for one when they need a damage dealer, so....do the job and deal the damage, which means evading and backstabbing.  You seem to have a different definition of "role" than I.  Yes I obviously realize that clerics can stun and nuke too, and other classes can do other things, and if it's something he should do in the group he's in, then that's part of his role too.  Don't doubt me.  Go ahead and continue how you play the rogue if you want, it doesn't hurt me at all, but don't plan on being any good at your class when you start getting high levels.  Later.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
